                {
                    "verdict": "malicious",
                    "analysis": "This is a sample of the Ragnar Locker ransomware. The malware first performs an anti-analysis check, terminating itself if the system locale matches a list of CIS countries (e.g., Russian, Ukrainian). It then proceeds to delete volume shadow copies using `vssadmin delete shadows /all /quiet` and `wmic.exe shadowcopy delete` to prevent recovery. The ransomware enumerates and terminates specific services and processes to unlock files for encryption. It then traverses all logical drives, encrypting files using a custom encryption algorithm (likely Salsa20) and a hardcoded public key. Encrypted files are renamed with the `.ragnar_[hash]` extension, and a ransom note named `RGNR_[hash].txt` is created and displayed using `notepad.exe`. The note contains a base64-encoded block labeled `---RAGNAR SECRET---`, which is the encrypted session key required for decryption.",
                    "source": "palm",
                    "category": "code_insight",
                    "id": "c2bd70495630ed8279de0713a010e5e55f3da29323b59ef71401b12942ba52f6-file-palm"
